      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">Quickest Way to Lose Weight</category>
      <title>What is the Quickest Way to Lose Weight Naturally and Safely?</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;By &lt;a href="http://ezinearticles.com/?expert=John_Cielo"&gt;John Cielo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;An often asked question is "What's the quickest way to lose weight?" And you have obviously asked it because you are reading this article. It could be because you have a wedding coming up, the office Christmas party, a beach holiday, or, you want to get your shape back after pregnancy, or any number of other reasons. Here, we'll explore together a way of achieving your goal, perhaps more easily than you suspected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The first thing to remember is a very simple balance equation, i.e. &lt;i&gt;calories in = calories out&lt;/i&gt;. Simply put, it means that if you can burn all the calories your body takes in through food and drink, you should not put on excess weight. And a key way you burn calories is through regular physical exercise. Unfortunately, the result of not burning enough calories is that the excess calories then turn to stored fat in your body.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But many people, like yourself, never achieve this &lt;i&gt;calorie balance&lt;/i&gt;. Why? Because most of us eat too much and do not take enough exercise to burn off those excess calories. In many cases this is as a direct result of our modern lifestyles. You are probably affected this way; in balancing work family commitments, you just do not have the time, or the energy, to do everything the TV chefs, dietary experts, and exercise gurus tell you to do. It is just so much hard work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So what is the quickest way to lose weight? Well, look at the equation. Simply put, you can either, drastically reduce your calorie intake (eat less food), or, burn up more calories (take more exercise). Or, as most people try to do; you can do both at the same time. Basically, you go on a dietary plan to reduce your calorie intake and start exercising in the gym and / or running around the streets and parks hoping to burn off your excess calories.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And this does work if you have the time and energy to follow through with this type of weight-loss plan. But as you have seen above most of us do not have the time, or, the energy. And because of this, even if you do start on this type of plan, with the best will in the world, you probably will fail in the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So how can you achieve this calorie balance and lose weight quickly? Think about it for a moment. If you could reduce your hunger pangs you would eat less, right? So your calorie intake would reduce, you would have less excess calories to burn off, so the amount of stored fat in your body would reduce. Alright then, how can you reduce your hunger pangs in a safe, controlled manner? The answer could lie in appetite suppressants. Or better still, &lt;i&gt;natural&lt;/i&gt; appetite suppressants, where the ingredient(s) come from natural resources such as plants.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are a number of dietary supplements out there which can suppress your appetite. But there is one which not only suppresses your appetite, but increases your metabolism at the same time, which helps to burn off even more of your stored fat, so that you lose weight even more quickly. It also claims to increase your energy levels so that you feel more energized and better all round.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Many people are now turning to these dietary supplements to achieve their weight-loss goals in a safe and easy way, and, which fits in with their busy lifestyles. This could be &lt;i&gt;your&lt;/i&gt; ideal dietary solution to your question; "What is the quickest way to lose weight?"&lt;/p&gt;


