      <category domain="http://www.blogger.com/atom/ns#">lose weight quick</category>
      <title>Lose Weight - Quick Tips to Help You Lose Weight</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;By &lt;a href="http://ezinearticles.com/?expert=Shannon_Clark"&gt;Shannon Clark&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;If you're currently trying to lose weight, you will definitely have to put in some effort. Far too many people are searching for a mystery fat loss technique that will get them losing pounds without much effort from their part. Unfortunately, if they proceed to follow these 'quick fix' plans, chances are, they will be highly disappointed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In order to lose weight you will have to make some adjustments to your current lifestyle and habits, but, if you are smart in how you go about doing this, it does not need to be all that bad.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are some quick tips that you can use to help you lose weight.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Get More Protein&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While you definitely don't need to go on an all-protein diet (which is strongly NOT recommended), foods that are higher in protein content will be much more satisfying than those that aren't.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not only does the body need slightly more protein when dieting in order to protect lean muscle mass, but it will also help you feel satisfied for a longer period of time, thus make watching your calorie intake all the more easier.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you're starving all the time, it makes it kind of hard to eat a low-calorie diet. Protein can help with this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Try Drinking More Hot Beverages&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Another easy trick to help with the hunger factor when dieting is to drink more hot beverages such as tea or coffee. Obviously you will need to pay attention to what you are adding to this - avoid any high calorie syrups, cream, or sugar, but the hot liquid in general will really tame your hunger.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Plus, if you do opt for a beverage that contains caffeine, that can give you an extra energy boost, which you might find you need while on a diet. You can overdo it with the caffeine, however, so be sure you monitor your intake appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Add Sprints To Your Workout&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Very few individuals enjoy doing cardio in their quest to lose weight, but, it is something that normally does have to be included in a program to some extent. So, why not at the very least, maximize the time you spend doing this cardio?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rather than performing thirty to forty-five minute sessions at a moderate pace - which is sure to bring on the boredom factor at an alarming rate, crank up the intensity with sprint sessions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sprint session are a great deal shorter - usually lasting from anywhere between fifteen and twenty-five minutes, and will ramp your metabolic rate up much higher after they are performed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, not only will you be spending less time on the cardio machines, but you'll get double the benefits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These are going to be more intense though, so be sure you do have some cardio based behind you. Work up to doing thirty minutes straight at a moderate intensity, then try incorporating some sprints into the program.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Take A Diet Break&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes! I know what you're thinking. "A diet break? How will that help me lose weight?!?" The answer is because far too many people are chronic dieters and because of this, their metabolism is already running slower than it should.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Every three to four months you should always bring your calorie intake up a bit, hold it there for a week or two, and then bring it back down again. This will help to 'reset' the metabolism again, increasing the rate at which you are burning calories and really making a difference in the results you see.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, if you're struggling to get that scale moving, be sure you keep these tips in mind. Nothing is more frustrating than putting in a great deal of effort to not experience any results.&lt;/p&gt;


