&lt;p&gt;You know, of course, that you are not the only person concerned about weight loss, especially before summertime and after Christmas!  You are probably really ready to rid yourself of that extra fat once and for all.  First, you must take a good look at your present state.  Are you over 40 and just beginning to get a roll around the middle?  Or perhaps you are a young mother who has just given birth for the first or third time?  Or, perhaps you are now working longer hours sitting at a desk or computer and the pounds are slipping up on you?  Is it possible that you are now in the state of life where terms such as "diabetes" and "heart disease" are beginning to take on new meaning as you begin to fit the profile of what you hear on a commercial?  Whatever your state, take heart there is hope!  And I will show you what and how to lose weight quick and change your body and change your life.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First, you must realize that the battleground consists of two phases - one is your daily stress and the only is your lean towards high-fat food.  The sad part is that this combination makes it very difficult to have the energy or desire to exercise which adds to more pounds.  Further, as we all know, trying to starve yourself backfires as your body holds onto to calories when you deliberately put into in a starvation state!  Amazingly, our bodies and our brain have a built-in signal to store fat.  Therefore, when you begin to try to lose fat, you find yourself working against this built-in mechanism.  Quick weight loss from starvation returns before you have time to brag about it!  You must learn how to turn off the fat-making mechanism and turn on and leave on the fat-burning mechanisms in your body.&lt;/p&gt;


